{{Commons category|Chrysler Pacifica}}
{{main|Chrysler Pacifica (1999 concept vehicle)|Chrysler Pacifica (crossover)|Chrysler Pacifica (minivan)}}

The '''Chrysler Pacifica''' nameplate was used by [[Chrysler]] for a variety of vehicles. It was first used on a luxury [[minivan]] concept vehicle in 1999. From 2004 to 2008, it was used on a mid-size [[crossover (automobile)|crossover]]. Since the 2017 model year, it has been used as the [[Chrysler Town & Country|Town & Country minivan]]'s replacement.

